data.name: Classic Bacon Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: A juicy beef patty topped with crispy bacon, melted cheese, and fresh toppings, all nestled in a soft bun.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat your grill or skillet over medium-high heat.
Form the ground beef into two equal-sized patties, making a slight indentation in the center of each.
Season both sides of the patties with salt and pepper.
Cook the patties for about 4-5 minutes on one side, then flip them over.
While the second side is cooking, add the bacon strips to the pan or grill and cook until crispy, about 5-6 minutes.
In the last minute of cooking the burger, place a slice of cheddar cheese on each patty to melt.
Toast the burger buns on the grill or in a toaster until golden brown.
Assemble the burgers by placing the patty on the bottom bun, adding crispy bacon, lettuce, tomato, and pickles. Spread ketchup and mustard on the top bun and place it on top.
Serve immediately with your choice of sides.
data.modifiersForBase: With crispy bacon and fresh toppings
